==<span style="font-family:Jost;">'''Description'''</span>==
{{Blurimage|file=DHS6.png|caption=A dim hallway photographed by a wanderer.}}
<div style="font-family:Jost; font-size:18px;">
Level 742 is a large multi-story school complex similar to a late 20th century middle or high school. Most wanderers enter on the central hallway which has a locker, bulletin boards, and classroom doors spaced out evenly along its length. While the building appears well maintained, with cleaned floorboards and walls, there are no signs of activity or life that is commonly found within a functional building; no school bells, announcements, or schedules have ever been recorded and the halls seem to eternally maintain silence. Sounds are not able to travel far at all in the building; even in longer halls, footstep or vocal sounds will eventually fade within short distances.

The building is coated in a faint but peculiar smell which smells similar to dust and the standard cleaning solutions found in a school environment along with another smell described as "organic" though not rotten or foul, the cause of this has not been determined and some individuals have noted it immediately, while others would only realize that the odor was present after several hours of exploration. Users of the space have claimed that the smell is very noticeable at this point, though the intensity differs from wanderer to wanderer and for unknown reasons.

Lights within the school either shine brightly down through ceiling lights or are absent without being broken/unpowered despite the lights looking undamaged, in sections where lights do not function there have been reports that none of the switches on the wall control any of them. Certain windows found in classrooms, stairwells, and select hallways display an unusual visual property. Rather than showing an exterior view, they appear uniformly washed out, presenting a flat, pale white surface.

{{Blurimage|file=DHS4.png|caption=An image of a classroom captured by an anonymous wanderer.}}

The classrooms resemble an abandoned classroom, with desks in neat rows, and the chalkboard or whiteboard filled with a writing that stops in mid-sentence, or calculation with a question left hanging at the end of a phrase, you can often find worksheets on desks that are half finished with answers that vary significantly in handwriting despite there being no writing implements.

The text on some whiteboards has been observed to alter between visits, at first the change only involves one word or symbol on the board being added, but as time passes they change more considerably. They will eventually start writing whole problems which vary in method of solution, neither of which have been known to be the correct one, when these changes are erased they often re appear, if left alone for long enough.

Writing utensils within the classrooms seem to only show very little wear, and may appear to move on their own after being left unobserved, some wanderers have also noted to hear the faint sound of chalk being drawn by itself from empty classrooms.

It is strongly advised not to spend an extensive amount of time within a classroom as it has been known to bring the sensation of expectation for completion, particularly when sitting at a desk; an unwillingness to leave will also occur if the feel of the classroom has set in too strongly. In rare instances, wanderers claim to remember that they have attended that class before, even when it clearly is not possible.

Along most of the halls there are lines of lockers. These are typically show some degree of age and/or wear (dents, scratches, doors being open or slightly damaged), but all lockers visited have been empty. The hallways are generally associated with an intensification of sensory experience, more specifically sounds. Smaller noises will often sound farther away than they really are, and movements can be observed in the periphery, once you stop to look there seems to be no source at all.

The restrooms are functional. The sinks will run, and toilets will flush. However, mirrors will act oddly; reflections will be delayed, incomplete, particularly regarding features such as the eyes; they will appear to age more the longer you stare into them and are considered the reason many people do not want to remain in the restrooms for long amounts of time.

Time operates in peculiar ways within Level 742; clocks are often out of sync with each other, stop, or don't work at all; and the light levels never change no matter how long you stay; mapping out the level has been proven impossible time after time. These events are strongly connected to [[Phenomenon 57]].

No hostile entities have been confirmed in the area. Even though it is thought to be a sustainable level for humans there are none inhabiting the level. It is common to experience confusion of time and a general feeling of mental exhaustion after spending a lot of time in this level, not injury though.

==<span style="font-family:Jost>'''Entrances & Exits'''==
===<span style="font-family:Jost>'''Entrances'''===
* In [[Level 718]] you can enter by opening a door in a silent ward that should lead to another patient room.
* In [[Level 740]] you can enter by leaving a theater hallway that has gone completely quiet.
* In [[Level 772]] you can enter by following a repetitive routine until the environment begins to resemble a school corridor.
* In [[Level 797]] you can enter by entering an abandoned building (near the Lusenau buildings) that resembles a school at night.

===<span style="font-family:Jost>'''Exits'''===
* Entering a music room where a piano is softly playing on its own "may" lead to [[Level 477]].
* Opening a locker that’s completely untouched and locked tight "might" lead to [[Level 655]].
* If you fall asleep inside the nurse's office, you "may" wake up in [[Level 450]].
* Rare stairwells marked “Staff Only” "may" lead directly to [[Level 678]].
* Peering into a classroom mirror and seeing a reflection that doesn't match "will" send you to [[Level 444]].
* Opening a janitor's closet that smells faintly of lemon and ozone "may" bring you into [[Level 447]].

